# SEO / GEO — BookedFox marketing (`bookedfox.com`)

Read `docs/marketing/seo-geo-playbook.md` and `tasks/seogeo/README.md` before editing marketing SEO.

## Indexation (non-negotiable)

**Index only:** `/`, `/privacy`, `/terms` on `https://bookedfox.com`.

**Never index:** `/app/*`, `/crew/*`, `/api/*`, `/sign-in`, `/sign-up`, `/auth/*`, `/book/*`, `/my/*`.

- `robots.txt` must `Disallow` those prefixes.
- Non-marketing layouts must export `robots: { index: false, follow: false }`.
- Do not add app or auth URLs to `sitemap.xml`.

## Phase-aware copy (`lib/config.ts`)

```ts
export const phase: LaunchPhase = "waitlist" | "launch";
```

- **All** title, meta description, OG text, CTAs, and schema `offers` read from config helpers — never hardcode waitlist copy in components.
- **Waitlist:** meta description ≤155 chars with waitlist CTA; schema `offers.availability` = `https://schema.org/PreOrder`.
- **Launch:** remove waitlist CTA; primary CTA → `/sign-up`; schema `offers.availability` = `https://schema.org/InStock`.
- Flipping `phase` must trigger SEO-05 checklist (`tasks/seogeo/sprint-seo-05-launch-phase-transition.md`).

## Title & meta rules

- `<title>`: brand **first** (`BookedFox | …`), ≤60 characters.
- `<meta name="description">`: ≤155 characters — use `seoMeta[phase].description`, not long `site.description`.
- `og:image` required (1200×630); `metadataBase` = `https://bookedfox.com`.

## JSON-LD

- Single `@graph` in **`<head>`**: Organization, WebSite, SoftwareApplication (`BusinessApplication`), FAQPage.
- `faqs` in `lib/config.ts` is single source for FAQ HTML + JSON-LD.
- Logo as `ImageObject`; `sameAs` only when real profile URLs exist.

## GEO HTML

- FAQ answers must be in SSR HTML (prefer `<details>` over client-only accordion).
- Feature lists: `<ul>/<li>` with `<strong>Title:</strong> description`.
- Use `<header>`, `<main>`, `<footer>`, `<section>`, `<article>`.

## After marketing SEO changes

```bash
npm run smoke:seo   # when implemented
npm run build
```

Update `CHANGELOG.md` if phase or indexation policy changes.

## Google Tag Manager (marketing only)

- Set `NEXT_PUBLIC_GTM_ID` (public container ID). Never commit real secrets — GTM ID is safe in env.
- GTM loads **only** on `marketingRoutes` paths (`lib/seo/marketing-paths.ts`), gated by `x-marketing-page` from `proxy.ts`.
- **Never** load GTM on `/app/*`, `/book/*`, `/crew/*`, auth, or portals.
- Adding a new indexable marketing page: update `marketingRoutes` in `lib/config.ts` + page metadata (`index: true`, canonical) — sitemap and GTM follow automatically.
